        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Hi friends \xf0\x9f\x91\x8b ,
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Happy Thursday!
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Every week, I record an audio edition of Not Boring. Typically the morning of the newsletter, I wake up at 5:30am, head to the basement, record, edit, pick music for, and publish a version of the essay that I read out loud. I have a face for radio and a voice for Twitter, but I like doing the audio version because it lets me give you another way to consume these essays that I spend so much time on.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Thing is, while anywhere between 30k - 100k people read each essay (thanks for sharing!), about 1,500 max listen to the audio version, despite the relative ease of consumption. A big part of the reason for the delta? Podcast discovery sucks.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Today, I\xe2\x80\x99m writing about
         <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkE2OwyAMhU9TllH4S8iCxWzmGogEN0UlQMHpKHP6ocliJMuWbD0_fW-xCGsqh86pIvk0g0cGHeGnBkCEQvYKxXin6cAUl2IiTgtHlVTEV3MvAJv1QWPZgeR9Dn6x6FM8FX3PJHloZUfKFbd2Gicx0slSLuldqlG6fpzv7PK1u_MQF9DwhnKkCCToB2KuN_51Y9-tgq8IEVNO7rdb0tZWNmfiNesZ7SlT7a-UQ0e7RbxBPl8oebqJfltZV_e5ol2eHx0pOiacU_Fxbefnw24QzkMDMG1ue_R4GIh2DuAuNrwiOmnNChFKi84Ziy0YSpVgVA6ipXOyNHhOJ6GGiZPm7FJTxX_TP6Myfoc" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
          Podz
         </a>
         , a company whose product I believe has the potential to change that. This is the first time I\xe2\x80\x99ve written a sponsored deep dive about a consumer social product - all of the rest have been fintech or investing-adjacent - because I assume that if you\xe2\x80\x99re the kind of person who takes the time to read Not Boring once or twice a week, you want to learn new things. I think Podz is going to make it a lot easier to find new audio content on the subjects you want to learn about, and make it easier for the people who, like me, spend hours behind a microphone recording.
        </p>
