        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         It\xe2\x80\x99s bizarre that the social audio opportunity is still up for grabs. Talking is the oldest form of communication, but while text-, photo-, and video-based consumer social each have both casual and quality winners, audio just joined the party in 2020. Clubhouse has taken the lead in
         <strong>
          casual
         </strong>
         social audio, but Podz is going after what I think may be the bigger prize: building the
         <strong>
          quality
         </strong>
         social audio feed that surfaces the best content we humans create with our voices.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         In April, I wrote one of my first Not Boring essays,
         <em>
          <strong>
           <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxVkM1uwyAQhJ8m3GLxYyx84NBLX8PCsDgoGBxYJ3KfvtSRWlUCVmg0O5rPGoQll0NvuSL5eSY8NtAJXjUCIhSyVyhTcJoNXAnZj8Tp3jElFQl18gVgNSFqLDuQbZ9jsAZDTqeDUi7JTfORU0_9TL0dhaSeG89AzNxT5TgD-841uwuQLGh4QjlyAhL1DXGrF_Fx4Z_tpIxzLiEtXd3nisbeO5vXJmztvto316tJ7vqV87pErCRoTjmjjCsmpJRDxzrbP0HeHyhFvvR0Xfi_XaTo35Am329mhXgKrdrU5rqngMcEycwR3Ls1vuGdHKYFEpQG1U0GGzLGVM-ZHPrG7WzZsAg29moYBWnJLjdX-gv9BqLBiRg" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
            Wackos and ZoomGl\xc3\xbcts
           </a>
          </strong>
         </em>
         , in which I used an old episode of
         <em>
          Hey Arnold
         </em>
         to explain why, at the same time:
        </p>
        <ol style="margin: 1em 0;">
         <li style="margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">
           It was so hard for podcasts and virtual events to stand out, and
          </p>
         </li>
         <li style="margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">
           The buzziest startup around was one that combined podcasts and virtual events.
          </p>
         </li>
        </ol>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         I was talking, of course, about
         <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkE2OgzAMhU_TLFGcHwYWWcym14hC4kKmkDDBFHH7SeliJMuWbD09f887wjGX06x5I_Zuls4VTcJjm5EIC9s3LDYGA63opFY9C0YF6HTH4mYfBXFxcTZUdmTrPszRO4o5XQrOhWaTcaID7DmGIH3vHhxASgQ3aAdcfz2Gj6_bQ8Tk0eALy5kTstlMROt2k983ca91HEfzk2Py8z5Muf7V-LzUPYtGcAEcqo_UWrcNNF69UD9_Sct8U3wZRbPtw0bOP98iVkzKNOQS01jPz8ktOF-HimDrXPYU6bSY3DBj-NDRJ6SL146YsNTwgnVUowHolADdqprPRVPxJfSqa3vJqnPIVZX-Tf8AmEyAHw" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
          Clubhouse
         </a>
         , the drop-in audio chat app that launched in March.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         It seemed crazy then. At the beginning of the quarantine, any brand, community, or family with a Zoom connection was hosting free events. Zoom fatigue set in fast and hard. Meanwhile, I wrote, \xe2\x80\x9cAt a time when podcast listening is down by 25%, Amazon sold out of podcast mics. Production is increasing even while demand plummets.\xe2\x80\x9d
        </p>
        <div class="captioned-image-container-static" style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin-bottom: 16px; text-align: center;">
