        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         No commute meant less time to listen to podcasts, but more time stuck inside and more uncertainty about job prospects meant more people wanted to try their hand at making podcasts, hence a podcast supply glut. Our earholes weren\xe2\x80\x99t wide enough to let everything in.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Clubhouse cut through the noise. By limiting invitations to a small group of tech Twitter illuminati, it manufactured exclusivity at a time when every other organization on earth was begging people to come to their free online event/happy hour/conversation/panel.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         \xe2\x80\x9cWhile everyone else is begging \xe2\x80\x98please!,\xe2\x80\x99\xe2\x80\x9d I wrote, \xe2\x80\x9cClubhouse is telling them \xe2\x80\x98no.\xe2\x80\x99 It\xe2\x80\x99s the one velvet rope in a world of two-for-one happy hours hawked by overeager promoters.\xe2\x80\x9d
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         It worked. In May, Clubhouse
         <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkEuOgzAMhk9DlihPCIssRhr1GigQl0ZAwgTTDrcfly5GsvxIZP_2N3qEKZfTbXlH9nY9nhu4BK99AUQo7Nih9DE40UirjO5YcDoIayyLe38vAKuPi8NyANuOYYmjx5jT1cG5NOzhGqu71kNQd5Bacz6EcdDt4I2gRJnw0fVHiJBGcPCEcuYEbHEPxG2v1Fclb2T4iu-N6jGvVPkFfsucU_GBqh09HjslQjZCyaZttW2tFVoKXqnb4tNUqW9ILDrJ6U1IK5QxpqlFPeonmPkHjcqV5usk6_0YaOA4v6VYcSnjkEukEZrPD7_Ccn3QuT3F9UgRzx6SHxYIHxL4AXqx6SdIUAh06D0SRiEsbWUaTSyvywmVEp22TacYKYdMXelf9A8Iaoxq" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
          announced
         </a>
         a $12 million, a16z-led Series A that valued the company at $100 million. The company was still in beta, had a couple thousand users, and no revenue. Thinkpeople were flummoxed.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         But here we are, nine months and eight decades\xe2\x80\x99 worth of quarantine later, and Clubhouse just raised a fresh $100 million Series B, once again
         <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkEtuxCAQRE8z7GLxtfGCRTa5hsWnx4PGBgfaEzmnD_YsIqFqpKK76OctwpzLYbZckZwy4bGBSfBTF0CEQvYKZYrBsJ5roeRIgpGBaaVJrNO9AKw2LgbLDmTb3RK9xZjT1UEpV-Rh4O6C5oIyEQav1KDcQJnno7bMuXHw71y7hwjJg4EXlCMnIIt5IG71Jj5v_Ksdy_rfzue1XTnlrBV6CpdNYnpBxZjmj5g-_LK7R24fbwaJ5nxMGddMKKX6jnVevkA9v1GJfJN0nXlXd1fR-uc5nhSTMrpc2rRmPx92heUy2n5Tq-ueIh4TJOsWCO_V8U3wgjHNkKA0smGy2LgxpiVnqpcN3rVqYyPYKHU_CtKSQ25d6T_0D_JShtw" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
          led by a16z
         </a>
         , this time valuing the business at $1 billion. This time, out of beta, with 2 million users, and plans for creator-focused revenue generation, people
         <em>
          get it.
         </em>
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Clubhouse\xe2\x80\x99s success is remarkable, but it isn\xe2\x80\x99t unique in the world of audio. In fact, after an early-pandemic dip, podcasts have come roaring back. Listening is up dramatically, all of the usual suspects are spending hundreds of millions on content, and more people are recording themselves talking than ever before.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Despite that, spoken-word audio is in the early innings of digitalization and monetization:
        </p>
        <ul style="margin: 1em 0;">
         <li style="margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">
           Podcast ad revenue is
           <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkcmOwyAMhp-m3IjClpADh7nMa0QsTosaIAOkmbz90PQwkuVFlv1bn62ucE_5VFsqFb3dXM8NVISjrFArZLQXyLN3igxUMsEn5BR3RAqJfJmXDBC0X1XNO6BtN6u3uvoUr4m-pwI9FIyjc4uzctB04ZaM0nHB2CCMHTkx5qOrd-chWlDwgnymCGhVj1q3cmNfN_rd7DiOTv_6VDqbQqu35KwuFZu9-AilYJNS8PGOFzhw0M93GtqiEzsx9D3pDRZMLpiPdMFmmRxmoKUDM41cyu5Rw4q8oj0lPaGSMCHE0JHO8heI508VLN14H-60K7spVdvn-w6UVUzVpNzUWvv50AHWq9FozC2GPfp6zhC1WcF9QNUP7wvdfIcIuf3Bzbo2yoRITokYeEN9gWkkGZm4HCaGmrJLbSr-i_4BbDmYhA" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
            projected
           </a>
           to grow 10x faster than the next closest medium over the next five years, and even then, it will bring in less than 10% of what radio does.
          </p>
         </li>
         <li style="margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">
           A tiny minority of podcasters take home the vast majority of the listens and dollars.
          </p>
         </li>
         <li style="margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">
           Clubhouse and Twitter Spaces are pushing audio-only public conversations forward.
          </p>
         </li>
         <li style="margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">
           Companies like Otter and Descript are making it easier than ever to capture and transcribe all sorts of conversations.
          </p>
         </li>
        </ul>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         And still, spoken word audio discovery is an absolute disaster. It\xe2\x80\x99s one of the things holding podcasts back.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         That\xe2\x80\x99s what
         <strong>
          <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkE1uxCAMhU8zLKPwl4YFi256DUTAk6AQSMGZKj19mWRRybIlW0_P33MWYc7l1HuuSN7N4LmDTvBTIyBCIUeFYoLXdGAjl0IRr4WnoxxJqOZZADYbosZyANmPKQZnMeR0KfqeSbLoj8k78Jz5QQiQbFLuqTwMaqDAmVDy9rWHD5AcaHhBOXMCEvWCuNcH_3ywr1YxVISEec_-t3N5aysSNOsZ7SkbKZdSDh3tnHiBXL9R8vwQ_Tazrh5TRevWt4gUnTJOuYQ0t_O62A3idWjfmza3IwU8DSQ7RfA3GN75XKhmhgSl5eaNxZYKpaNgVDY2dYM0ck6VGAfFSXP2uanSv-kf_Qp-PA" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
           Podz
          </a>
         </strong>
         is working to fix, and the product is magical. Podz uses machine learning to pull the best clips from podcasts and deliver them to listeners in personalized feeds. Whenever you hear \xe2\x80\x9cmachine learning\xe2\x80\x9d or \xe2\x80\x9cAI,\xe2\x80\x9d you should be skeptical, and I was too, until Podz sent me three clips of my own podcast. It picked highlights better than I could myself, pulling out the thesis from each (
         <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkEFuhDAMRU8zWSLsJBQWWXTTa6CQGCYaSGhipqKnb4ZZVLJsS1_213_OMi0pn2ZPhcWrjXzuZCL9lJWYKYujUB6DN9BhL7UahDfKQ697Eco4Z6LNhtVwPkjsx7QGZzmkeF20LWpxN9rOs9MtqA-QpLAFJNd1SFZKNUts37728IGiI0NPymeKJFZzZ97LTX7e8KvW7n9L41LdpBwQCdQAH07ZyQ-vbwRutv2As0IRDLYI1akHqbXuGmicepJ-fLOW6ababcGmHFNh6x715yayiYmnlENcqvy4243WS6ihxjq3IwY-R4p2Wsm_8_Ib20VgXChSrjj9aLnCAugVgu5UJXblq0AkDKrvBimqs0_1Kv6b_gGfEYJo" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
          here
         </a>
         ,
         <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkM2OhCAQhJ9mOBpAUDxw2Mu-BuGndcgouNDOxn36ZfWwSYcmqRRFfd4iLLmces8Vyd9h8NxBJ_iuKyBCIUeFYmLQbOCql2IiQYvAlFQkVjMXgM3GVWM5gOyHW6O3GHO6HJRySZ7aC0_DyMZJ0Zl6N9qZCcrpyCdnJyrUnWuPECF50PCGcuYEZNVPxL0--o8H_2yzh5_a-dxuzTXPs2PBKSeUHxRw4KOFHlgYBt--pjnljDKuWC-lHDrWefEG-fpC2eeHoNvCu3q4ita_2psbKTpldLnEtDT59bQbrJfQSpm2tyNFPA0k61YId1-8sV0EzAIJSsMZjMUGizElOJODaMSufg1IzyahhqknLTnk5kr_ob8u84MT" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
