        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Podcasts also severely lag radio and TV in terms of monetization, which speaks to the opportunity in front of the industry.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         The global radio advertising industry is a
         <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkN1uwyAMhZ-m3DUKfw1ccLGbvUZEwE1RCWRAmuXt56WTJiFjY_sc8TnbYM7lMGuujfyGsR0rmAR7jdAaFLJVKGPwht6Y4lJo4o3wVElFQh3vBWCxIZpWNiDrNsXgbAs5nRt9zyR5GO2nnoLQd-kGxe8aPHhnGdfDoJQf_NvXbj5AcmDgBeXICUg0j9bWeuEfF_aJZ9_3rjaUx9C5vODTXxlcxYINTIsBkznmycZrsT7kq_Woh0MhzVf4XiH50LYCOEaCYT2jPWWKcinlraOdEy-Qz68meb6IfplZV7cJXdzz15EUk3KbckExbD8fdoF4NvDrI97LlkI7Rkh2iuDfVNob7slpnCFBQeh-tA2RUqoEo_ImkOtJAbFxqoW6aU7Q2WfcSv-mP40elAA" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
          $35 billion industry
         </a>
         . Based on the earnings of the top
         <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkU2u4yAQhE8TdljmzzYLFrOZa1ht6MQoGDy4_aLcfnAy0kgIEEVRzdceCB-lvt1eDmLXNNN7R5fxdSQkwsrOA-scgxODnJTRlgWng5jMxOIx3yviBjE5qiey_VxS9ECx5I-j76VhqxNiVGHAXhvrvQjGWO1l6M2oINz1Yr-5cIaI2aPDH6zvkpEltxLtN_XrJn-38Xq9upiPGLBCiKXzZWunVwWXSGXnzxgPft_4tU_FQ-KfmzxmXtur-UR-L5XT2gxQKfqE8ygDBDDAh1EuXAi0HBajuVB2UCP0woPtVtoSi072UvRCTkIZY4ZOdF7_oHn-IaPKTffbQ3bHuRwE_nlVx6rLhZZSY340-bnChukjNFBzW7czR3rPmGFJGL4M6duKD9X5gbl9ljDMQK0BQkxaCjNo_Y9Zg6yE1dNgFWvJoTRX_h_6Fz39oPA" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
          10 radio stations in the US
         </a>
         , spoken word radio stations (news/sports) account for 57% of revenues. Applying that same percentage to the overall market, spoken word audio advertising is a $20 billion market before applying any sophisticated data or targeting.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Worldwide TV ad spend is five times larger than radio, coming in at $166 billion in 2019.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         By contrast, podcasting is still tiny. PWC estimates $812 million in podcast ad revenue globally for 2020, but projects that that number will grow at a 22% CAGR through 2024, at which point it expects the industry to generate $1.7 billion in ad revenue.
        </p>
        <div class="captioned-image-container-static" style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin-bottom: 16px; text-align: center;">
         <figure style="display: inline-block; margin: 0 auto; width: 100%;">
          <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="image-wrapper" style="margin: 8px auto; mso-padding-alt: 1em 0 1.6em;" width="100%">
           <tbody>
            <tr>
             <td style="text-align: center;">
